      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "1. Identify the flaky tests and isolate the timing issues by adding explicit waits or retries in the Playwright tests.\n2. Use a combination of headless and full browser modes to ensure the tests run consistently.\n3. Implement a custom test runner that retries failed tests up to 3 times before marking them as failed.\n4. Add a pre-check script that runs before the test suite to ensure the backend services are stable and ready for testing.\n5. Use a mock server to simulate backend responses and eliminate race conditions.\n6. Integrate a reporting tool that highlights flaky tests and provides insights for future improvements.\n7. Set up a CI/CD pipeline that runs the test suite in parallel to reduce execution time and increase the chances of passing.\n8. Use a code coverage tool to ensure all critical paths are tested and add any missing tests.\n9. Implement a post-test cleanup script to reset the environment and prevent state leakage between tests.\n10. Schedule a meeting with the development team to discuss the flaky tests and work together to resolve the issues before the deployment.",
