    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "```javascript\nconst { chromium } = require('playwright');\n\n(async () => {\n  const browser = await chromium.launch();\n  const context = await browser.newContext();\n  const page = await context.newPage();\n\n  // Login flow\n  await page.goto('https://cloudscale.example.com/login');\n  await page.fill('input[name=\"username\"]', 'testuser');\n  await page.fill('input[name=\"password\"]', 'testpass');\n  await page.click('button[type=\"submit\"]');\n  await page.waitForSelector('div.dashboard', { state: 'visible' });\n\n  // Assertions for login and dashboard loading\n  const dashboardExists = await page.isVisible('div.dashboard');\n  console.assert(dashboardExists, 'Dashboard should be visible after login');\n\n  // Close the browser\n  await browser.close();\n})();\n```\nThis script uses Playwright to automate the login flow and checks if the dashboard is visible after login. It waits for the dashboard element to be visible before making the assertion, which should help with the timing issues. If you need more tests or modifications, let me know.",
